changelog:

  • Java 21
  • Minecraft 1.21.5
  • neoforge 21.5.14-beta

  • See http://journeymap.info for information about how to install and use this mod, rules about inclusion in modpacks, translation, etc.
  • See http://journeymap.info for information on getting technical support.
  • Implements JourneyMap API v2.0.0

CHANGELOG (2025-05-04-14:33:21):

New in 1.21.5-6.0.0-beta.45

  • Added: New button to waypoint manager to configure some editor options.
  • Added: In Waypoint Options: "X, Y, Z", "X, Z, Y", or "Single field" for coordinate input in the waypoint editor.
  • Added: Auto backup of WaypointData.dat file on load. Will load backup if issues are found with main file.
  • Added: Waypoint Groups can use custom icons for all waypoints in the group.
  • Added: In Waypoint Options: Using a single Actions button or multi buttons for waypoints in the waypoint manager.
  • Added: Server Admin option to disable minimap.
  • Added: Server Admin option to disable all coordinate displays. (Does not affect existing waypoint names)
  • Added: API Hook to disable minimap.
  • Added: New option in Minimap Position screen to hide effect icons.
  • Added: Cartography Option: Map only player chunk
  • Added: Waypoint Option to display Player Heads in world.
  • Added: When updating the x and z values of a waypoint, it will pull the top-y value from cache if it exists.
  • Changed: Cleaned up the Waypoint Manager, a bit less cluttered with Actions Button enabled, made buttons a bit larger.
  • Changed: Moved server disabling/enabling to info logs instead of debug.
  • Changed: Default vanilla teleport command to use "/execute in {dim} run tp {name} {x} {y} {z}"
  • Changed: Villager Icon for flat theme images, added a bit of gaussian blur.
  • Changed: Cleaned up the Waypoint Manager, a bit less cluttered, made buttons a bit larger. Please give feedback.
  • Fixed: MiniMap self arrow is drawn under other icons.
  • Fixed: Some color issues.
  • Fixed: Horses rendering on map.
  • Fixed: Minimap points and rim getting flipped
  • Fixed: File theme and webmap asset extraction on some linux distros.
  • Fixed: Importing and migrating ancient waypoints (1.7.10/1.12.2)
  • Fixed: Custom theme minimap frame persists when switching themes.
  • Fixed: Automap on unlimited height worlds.
  • Fixed: Mouse may get stuck dragging the map while switching themes.
  • Fixed: Biome map mapping water with mapBathymetry enabled.
  • Fixed: Popup menus do not close completely when clicking on an item.
  • Fixed: Some issues with the map on MacOS Retina displays.
  • Fixed: Api overlay titles at mouse position not rendering.
  • Fixed: Horse pets breaking entity radar rendering.
  • Fixed: ModCompat amecs-reborn
  • Fixed: Waypoint Icon issues when removing an icon resource pack.
  • Fixed: Cave automapping not displaying lights.
  • Fixed: Fullscreen Map text bars not always in the correct position

CHANGELOG (2025-04-04-16:06:28):

New in craftmine-6.0.0-beta.44

  • Added: New Minimap orientation, Vertical Rectangle. Old Rectangle is now named Horizontal Rectangle
  • Added: Waypoints Option to open waypoint manager in your current dimension.
  • Added: Addon Option when Pixelmon or Cobblemon are installed to hide or display Pokemon independent of hide animals option.
  • Added: Waypoint group tags to prefix on waypoint names for the group, only works on custom groups.
  • Added: Warning text to automap when c2me is installed.
  • Changed: Waypoints can be added/removed from the temp group, via dragging in the manager or editing/creation screen.
  • Fixed: Errors from journeymap if the server crashes, giving a false negative when JM tries to access the crashed server.
  • Fixed: Memory leak when previewing minimap.
  • Fixed: Minimap incorrectly shifting position when moving infoslots.
  • Fixed: Beacon Rendering when shaders are used.
  • Fixed: Marker and Image overlays uses MapImage blur incorrectly.
  • Fixed: Overlay texts with opacity 0 are displayed anyway.
  • Fixed: [Fabric]: Some mods that modify chat break waypoint chat sharing.
  • Fixed: Waypoint Icons not showing on webmap
  • Fixed: Semi-rare crash when deleting the map in game.
  • Fixed: ModCompat issues with ImmediatelyFast for waypoints and minimap.

  • Added: Advanced Option to disable rendering of the minimap behind screens.
  • Fixed: Map not clearing old dimension map tiles for some custom servers that do not update the player's dimension.
  • Fixed: Issue with mipmaps not getting uploaded to gpu for some users

  • Fixed: Issues with water when automapping topography maps.
  • Change: Disable mipmapping for arc gpus due poor opengl support.

name: journeymap-1.21.1-6.0.0-beta.33+neoforge
changelog:
JourneyMap 1.21.1-6.0.0-beta.33 for Minecraft 1.21.1

Requirements:

  • Java 21
  • Minecraft 1.21.1
  • neoforge 21.1.55

General Information:

  • See http://journeymap.info for information about how to install and use this mod, rules about inclusion in modpacks, translation, etc.
  • See http://journeymap.info for information on getting technical support.
  • Implements JourneyMap API v2.0.0

CHANGELOG (2025-01-12-15:11:43):

New in 1.21.1-6.0.0-beta.33

  • Added: Force purge all images from memory before exiting game.
  • Changed: Adjusted how modded flowerblock colors are calculated. Please report any issues.
  • Fixed: Enabling rendering of an Overworld waypoint in the nether changes waypoint position.
  • Fixed: Issues when using the mousebutton to open/close the fullscreen map.
  • Fixed: More fixes in place to prevent CCMs when getting waypoints to render and added better logging.
  • Fixed: Cobblemon NPC Icons
  • Fixed: Region tiles not getting cleaned properly when switching dimensions.
  • Fixed: Display Update not getting called when closing the fullscreen map.
  • Fixed: Waypoint command crashing servers sometimes.
  • Fixed: Regions of the map appear brighter when teleporting.
  • Fixed: Errors when resources packs use invalid namespace names.
  • Fixed: Weird issues with very old data.
  • Fixed: Mod Compat, immersive portals
  • Fixed: Modded leaves colors using or not using the biome color incorrectly.
  • Fixed: Another Waypoint crash...
  • Fixed: Icons and grid vibrate when the player moves.

name: journeymap-1.21-6.0.0-beta.23+neoforge
changelog:
JourneyMap 1.21-6.0.0-beta.23 for Minecraft 1.21

Requirements:

  • Java 21
  • Minecraft 1.21
  • neoforge 21.0.43-beta

General Information:

  • See http://journeymap.info/ for information about how to install and use this mod, rules about inclusion in modpacks, translation, etc.
  • See http://journeymap.info/Support for information on getting technical support.
  • Implements JourneyMap API v2.0.0

CHANGELOG (2024-09-04-20:20:39):

New in 1.21-6.0.0-beta.23

  • Added: Map Option to show offscreen players.
  • Added: New InfoSlot: Minecraft Day, know how many minecraft days you have played!
  • Added: Advanced Option: Disable mob icon fade based on vertical distance from player.
  • Added: Fullscreen Option to hide the theme button on the fullscreen map.
  • Added: Waypoint Option to enable/disable rendering of waypoints (key bind for this exists already).
  • Added: Waypoint Option to enable/disable rendering of waypoints in world and key bind.
  • Added: Waypoint Option to enable/disable rendering of waypoints on map and key bind.
  • Added: Waypoint Option Auto-Hide Icon range
  • Added: Waypoint Option Auto-Hide Label range
  • Added: Waypoint Option Auto-Hide Icon range
  • Added: Waypoint Option to remove decimals from /tp command.
  • Added: Waypoint Option to disable share waypoint, also removes the chat position from right click menu in fullscreen map.
  • Added: Minimap Options to move infoslots to the top or bottom of the minimap.
  • Added: Cartography Option to ignore snow, this may have weird effects.(experimental and may be removed in the future)
  • Added: Two house looking waypoint icons.
  • Added: Group button to enable/disable group.
  • Added: MapImage disable or enable blur on images.
  • Added: Server Option to disable/enable right click teleporting on full map when waypoint teleport is enabled.
  • Added: Server Options to adjust radar ranges and entity counts.
  • Added: Server Option to adjust max cave render distance.
  • Added: Server Option to disable player names with player radar.
  • Added: Waypoint Manager button to import external waypoints from Xaeros. Button only exists if xaero's waypoints are detected.
  • Changed: Server Option max render distance changed to Max Surface render distance.
  • Changed: Game Time Real Info slot time format option to Info Slot Game Time Format. This also effects the Game Time infoslot.
  • Changed: InfoSlot Game Time Real name to "Game Time with Offset". To reflect the real world time offset.
  • Changed: Waypoint Option "Show Icon" to "Auto-Hide Icon"
  • Changed: Webmap port increased to allow up to 65535.
  • Changed: Default Player display to Outlined Icons.
  • Fixed: Offscreen waypoints not showing on the top or left side of fullscreen map.
  • Fixed: Crash when opening waypoint manager if a group is saved with a color override but no color set.
  • Fixed: Unable to update group color unless user disables and enables color override value.
  • Fixed: Edit waypoint button partially offscreen in gui scale 4.
  • Fixed: Exception being thrown from a null server if the server crashes by another mod.
  • Fixed: Unable to update waypoints, broke this in beta.22.
  • Fixed: AutoHide waypoint label option.
  • Fixed: Leaves colors do not use the biome tint.
  • Fixed: Effects do not respect minimap when changing gui-scale or minecraft window size.
  • Fixed: Possible naming issue when joining a realms server from the launcher.

name: journeymap-1.21-6.0.0-beta.21+neoforge
changelog:
JourneyMap 1.21-6.0.0-beta.21 for Minecraft 1.21

Requirements:

  • Java 21
  • Minecraft 1.21
  • neoforge 21.0.43-beta

General Information:

  • See http://journeymap.info/ for information about how to install and use this mod, rules about inclusion in modpacks, translation, etc.
  • See http://journeymap.info/Support for information on getting technical support.
  • Implements JourneyMap API v2.0.0

CHANGELOG (2024-08-28-17:17:09):

New in 1.21-6.0.0-beta.21

  • Added: Tooltip to dimensions panel in waypoint editor.
  • Added: Add waypoints that were shared from Xaeros via chat.
  • Added: New Multiplayer Debug options for Server Admins, with JourneyMap loaded chunks can be viewed on the map.
  • Added: Cartography options to adjust the max height for topography calculations. This will ensure old worlds loaded with the new build heights won't break topo maps.
  • Added: Hotkey to enable/disable waypoints.
  • Added: Button to waypoint panel to enable / disable visible waypoints.
  • Added: Group CRUD operations to ClientAPI.
  • Added: Support for AMECS fork too many shortcuts
  • Added: Button to fill a palette with default colors
  • Fixed: Some dimension issues with waypoint chat sharing
  • Fixed: API setting waypoint icon will now have a default of 16x16 texture size.
  • Fixed: Sometimes players remain on map after disconnect on velocity servers.
  • Fixed: Wierd border issues on dropdown/popup menus.
  • Fixed: Cache not saving Biome Key correctly when automapping.
  • Fixed: Log spam if server disables deathpoints and user has never had a deathpoint.
  • Fixed: Fullscreen slice slider when nether heights are not default.
  • Fixed: Crash with Flachback mod replays.
  • Fixed: Waypoints occupying the same X Z coordinates.
  • Updated: Spanish translations and added more spanish variants.
  • Changed: Improved waypoint text when shared via chat.
  • Changed: The existing hotkey for toggle waypoints changed to toggle rendering, this only disables rendering.
  • Changed: Clearing some state on server when exiting game.
  • Removed: Old waypoint manager code and options associated with it.
